AcceptedAnswer:
Your way is absolutely fine.  As you note, there is in fact an easier way.  It would be enough to show that the element $c$ such that $(ab)c = e$ is in fact $c = b^{-1} a^{-1}$: $$\begin{align}
(ab)b^{-1} a^{-1} &= a (b b^{-1}) a^{-1}
\\
&= a e a^{-1}
\\
&= a a^{-1}
\\
&= e.
\end{align}$$
